<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="turn-n">turn <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /tɜːn/    美 /tɜːrn/  </p>
<p>[C]</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>转动：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Give the handle a few turns. 
转动几下把手。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>翻动；翻身：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>With a few turns, she slept again.
她翻了几次身又睡着了。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>(车辆的) 转弯； (道路的) 弯道：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>take a turn to the right / left 
向右/左转弯</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.<strong>(异乎寻常或意外的) 转变；变化：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a horrible <strong>turn of events</strong>
可怕的事态变化</p><footer>2016 浙江</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>give a new turn to the argument 
把辩论引到一个新的方面</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Two days after the operation, Dad <strong>took a turn for the better</strong> / worse(= suddenly got better / worse)<strong>worse_1</strong>
手术两天后，爸爸的病情好转/恶化了。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.★ <strong>(依次轮到的) 机会：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It’s</strong> finally our <strong>turn to</strong> do the wallboard in the school hall!
终于轮到我们负责学校礼堂的墙报了！</p><footer>北师大② – 6</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="by-turns">by turns</h3>
<p>1.<strong>轮流；交替：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Leaving home for the first time he felt cheerful and sad by turns. 
第一次离开家，他时而高兴时而悲伤。</p></div>

<h3 id="in-turn">in turn</h3>
<p>1.<strong>依次；反过来；转而：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They answered the teacher’s questions in turn. 
他们依次回答了老师的问题。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The customer praised the manager, who, in turn praised his staff.  
顾客表扬了经理，经理转而表扬了员工。</p><footer>北师大③ – 8</footer></div>

<h3 id="take-turns">take turns</h3>
<p>1.<strong>轮流；依次：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They <strong>took turns</strong> ( <strong>in</strong> ) <strong>driving</strong>. 
他们轮流开车。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We <strong>take turns to do</strong> the housework. 
我们轮流做家务。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>With inspiration from other food cultures, American food culture can take a <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ for the better.   （2013 江苏）<br />
A. share<br />
B.chance<br />
C.turn <br />
D.lead  </li>
<li>People try to avoid public transportation delays by using their own cars, and <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (反过来) this creates further problems.   </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. C  2. in turn  </p></div>